   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step id="AddLocation" class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To find the appropriate location and draw the location geometries on the map, perform  the following steps:</cmd>
            <substeps id="Location_SubStepsOnly" class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To find the appropriate location on the map, perform  the following steps:</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Drag the map in the required direction.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Find address or place</uicontrol> box, enter the name of the location, click <image href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-Search.png"
                                     class="- topic/image "
                                     placement="inline">
                                 <alt class="- topic/alt ">Search</alt>
                              </image>, and then click the appropriate location.</p>
                           <p class="- topic/p ">The map of the area is displayed.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Use <image href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-Zoomout.png"
                                     class="- topic/image "
                                     placement="inline">
                                 <alt class="- topic/alt ">Zoom Out</alt>
                              </image> or <image href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-Zoomin.png"
                                     class="- topic/image "
                                     placement="inline">
                                 <alt class="- topic/alt ">Zoom In</alt>
                              </image> to zoom in or out on the map.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Select the appropriate base map from the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Base Map </uicontrol>drop-down list.</p>
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Available options are base maps defined in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">BASE MAPS</uicontrol> section in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">GIS Settings</uicontrol> page of the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Administration </uicontrol>module. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For more information, refer to <xref href="../../Mind/Administration/System_Configurations/GIS/GIS_Settings/GIS_Configuration.dita"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">Adding Base Maps</xref>.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">To view layers such as stations or transit centers, select the required layers in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Layer(s)</uicontrol> section.</p>
                           <p class="- topic/p ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Layer(s) </uicontrol>displayed in blue will only display features added in other records of this form.</p>
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Available options are base maps defined in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">LAYERS </uicontrol>section in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">GIS Settings</uicontrol> page of the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Administration</uicontrol> module. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For more information, refer to <xref href="../../Mind/Administration/System_Configurations/GIS/GIS_Settings/GIS_Configuration.dita"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">Adding Layers</xref>.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Add Feature</uicontrol> drop-down list, select the required feature to mark on the map.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The drawing toolset will display options based on the configured geometry corresponding to the selected feature.</info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To draw the location geometries, perform the following steps:</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">To mark a point on the map, click <image width=".5cm"
                                  href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-Point.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Location Point</alt>
                           </image>, and then click on the map at the required location.
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">To draw a polyline, click <image href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-PolyLine1.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Polyline</alt>
                           </image>, and then click on the map. To complete the boundary, follow the instructions as displayed on the map.
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">To draw a freehand polyline, click <image href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-PolyLine2.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Freehand Polyline</alt>
                           </image>, and then click on the map. To complete the boundary, follow the instructions as displayed on the map.
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">To draw a triangle, rectangle, or a circle, click <image href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-Triangle.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Triangle</alt>
                           </image>, <image href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-Rectangle.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Rectangle</alt>
                           </image>, or <image href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-Circle.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Circle</alt>
                           </image>, click on the map, and drag to size the map marker.
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">To mark a boundary, click <image href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-Polygon.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Polygon</alt>
                           </image> or <image href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-FreehandPoly.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Freehand Polygon</alt>
                           </image>, and then click on the map.
                            <p class="- topic/p ">To complete the boundary, follow the instructions as displayed on the map.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">To draw an arrow mark, click <image href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-Arrow.png"
                                  class="- topic/image "
                                  placement="inline">
                              <alt class="- topic/alt ">Arrow</alt>
                           </image>, and then click on the map and drag to size the map marker.
                        </li>
                     </ul>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Optionally, to update the location geometries drawn on the map, perform the appropriate actions, as described in the following table.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <table colsep="1" rowsep="1" class="- topic/table ">
                        <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                           <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="25%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                           <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="75%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                           <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                              <row class="- topic/row ">
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">Action</entry>
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">Steps</entry>
                              </row>
                           </thead>
                           <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                              <row class="- topic/row ">
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">Edit</entry>
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                    <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                                       <li class="- topic/li ">Right-click in a boundary or on a line, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Edit</uicontrol>.
                                    <p class="- topic/p ">Points that are editable are displayed.</p>
                                       </li>
                                       <li class="- topic/li ">Click a point and drag to edit the marker.
                                </li>
                                    </ol>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                              <row class="- topic/row ">
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">Move</entry>
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                    <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                                       <li class="- topic/li ">Right-click in a boundary or on a line, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Move</uicontrol>.
                                </li>
                                       <li class="- topic/li ">Click and drag the map marker to the required location on the map.
                                </li>
                                    </ol>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                              <row class="- topic/row ">
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">Rotate</entry>
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                    <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                                       <li class="- topic/li ">Right-click in a boundary or on a line, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Rotate</uicontrol>.
                                </li>
                                       <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Mind/Icons/Loc-Rotate.jpg"
                                                 class="- topic/image "
                                                 placement="inline">
                                             <alt class="- topic/alt ">Rotate</alt>
                                          </image>, and drag to rotate the marker.
                                </li>
                                    </ol>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                              <row class="- topic/row ">
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">Scale</entry>
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                    <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                                       <li class="- topic/li ">Right-click in a boundary or on a line, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Scale</uicontrol>.
                                </li>
                                       <li class="- topic/li ">Click a point and drag to adjust the marker boundary.
                                </li>
                                    </ol>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                              <row class="- topic/row ">
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">Delete</entry>
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                    <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                                       <li class="- topic/li ">Right-click in a boundary or on a line to be deleted.
                                </li>
                                       <li class="- topic/li ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Delete</uicontrol>.
                                    <p class="- topic/p ">A confirmation message is displayed.</p>
                                       </li>
                                       <li class="- topic/li ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">OK</uicontrol>.
                                </li>
                                    </ol>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                           </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                     </table>
                  </info>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
      </steps>
   </taskbody>
